President Obama and First Lady Michelle Obama have extended their warmest wishes to Buddhists around the world in their celebration of Vesak, a day that honors the birth, enlightenment, and passing of Buddha. They reflect on Buddha's teachings of peace, service, and recognition of common humanity, which are shared values that bind Americans together. The Obamas also acknowledge the contributions of Buddhists to progress and express their commitment to building a brighter future for all communities, cultures, and religions. They send their best wishes for wisdom, courage, and compassion during this season.